"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Littlefield was born in 1500, in Staplehurst, Kent, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Austin Littlefield, was 46 and his mother, Elizabeth Presten, was 38. He had at least 1 son with Margaret Wrigley. He died in 1567, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1500–1567":"1500–1567","1522–1550":"1522–1550","1530–1605":"1530–1605","1454–1520":"1454–1520","1462–1525":"1462–1525","1525":"1525","1567":"1567","1500":"1500","1522":"1522","1520":"1520","1454":"1454","15 April 1530":"15. aprill 1530","1530":"1530","1550":"1550","1462":"1462","1482":"1482","1605":"1605","Titchfield, Hampshire, England":"Titchfield, Hampshire, England","Staplehurst, Kent, England":"Staplehurst, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Yalding, Kent, England":"Yalding, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Tenterden, Kent, England":"Tenterden, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Trowbridge, Wiltshire, England":"Trowbridge, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1500–1567":"1500–1567","1522–1550":"1522–1550","1530–1605":"1530–1605","1454–1520":"1454–1520","1462–1525":"1462–1525","1525":"1525","1567":"1567","1500":"1500","1522":"1522","1520":"1520","1454":"1454","15 April 1530":"15. huhtikuuta 1530","1530":"1530","1550":"1550","1462":"1462","1482":"1482","1605":"1605"